Here's how to implement all three requirements:

**1 & 2. Intercept back navigation with a confirmation dialog**

Override `OnBackButtonPressed` in your page:

```csharp
public partial class EditProductPage : ContentPage
{
    private bool _hasUnsavedChanges;

    protected override bool OnBackButtonPressed()
    {
        if (!_hasUnsavedChanges)
            return base.OnBackButtonPressed();

        // Fire-and-forget since the override is synchronous
        Dispatcher.Dispatch(async () =>
        {
            bool leave = await DisplayAlert(
                "Unsaved Changes",
                "You have unsaved changes. Discard and go back?",
                "Discard", "Stay");

            if (leave)
                await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("..");
        });

        return true; // Cancel the default navigation
    }
}
```

> **Note:** `OnBackButtonPressed` only fires for the **hardware/OS back button** (Android). It does **not** fire when the user taps Shell's navigation bar back arrow.

**3. Replace the Shell back arrow with a custom "Cancel" toolbar button**

Hide the default back button and add your own:

```xml
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             x:Class="MyApp.EditProductPage"
             Shell.BackButtonBehavior="{StaticResource CancelBackButton}">

    <ContentPage.Resources>
        <BackButtonBehavior x:Key="CancelBackButton"
                            TextOverride="Cancel"
                            Command="{Binding BackCommand}" />
    </ContentPage.Resources>
    <!-- ... -->
</ContentPage>
```

Or set it inline:

```xml
<Shell.BackButtonBehavior>
    <BackButtonBehavior TextOverride="Cancel"
                        Command="{Binding BackCommand}" />
</Shell.BackButtonBehavior>
```

Then in your view model (or code-behind):

```csharp
[RelayCommand]
async Task Back()
{
    if (!_hasUnsavedChanges)
    {
        await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("..");
        return;
    }

    bool leave = await Shell.Current.DisplayAlert(
        "Unsaved Changes",
        "You have unsaved changes. Discard and go back?",
        "Discard", "Stay");

    if (leave)
        await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("..");
}
```

**Key points:**
- `BackButtonBehavior.Command` replaces the nav-bar arrow's default action, so returning from `Back()` without navigating effectively cancels navigation.
- `OnBackButtonPressed` covers the Android hardware back button separately.
- Setting `TextOverride="Cancel"` replaces the arrow with text. Use `IconOverride` if you want a custom icon instead.
